body:
I tried to use the app, but lost connection to the server. Checking the ManageAccountActivity showed me, that my Account state was offline. Disabling and enabling the account results in a short "online" and blinks later back to "offline" state.

I debugged into the application and found that the processStream function in eu.siacs.conversations.xmpp.XmppConnection.java is called three times. Once for the original tag and twice recursive during switch over to TLS.

Unfortunately this means that at the end of the tag parsing while loop it sets my account back to offline, because of the following lines:
```Java
if (account.getStatus() == Account.State.ONLINE) {
  account. setStatus(Account.State.OFFLINE);
  if (statusListener != null) {
    statusListener.onStatusChanged(account);
  }
}
```

My stacktrace looks like:
processStream():386, XmppConnection
processStream():289, XmppConnection
switchOverToTls():565, XmppConnection
processStream():275, XmppConnection
connect():213, XmppConnection
run():262, XmppConnection
run():818, Thread

I'm not sure about the process here and don't know the standards, but I suppose to skip the code quoted above during recursive calls. When executed once the account is offline and the code above does no harm, but during the recursive calls it kicks me out... Maybe you can remove the code at all?
